Sometimes when using the closure compiler, it's nice to be able to select what level each diagnostic group is reported at. I have written some code which will allow you to do this. 

We are using this so that our build will fail for most closure warnings, but not on missing properties, as it's going to take a while to get rid of all of those.

Example:
&lt;jscomp compilationlevel=&quot;simple&quot; warning=&quot;verbose&quot; debug=&quot;false&quot; output=&quot;${out}&quot;&gt;
    &lt;warning group=&quot;MISSING_PROPERTIES&quot; level=&quot;WARNING&quot;/&gt;
    &lt;warning group=&quot;DEPRECATED&quot; level=&quot;ERROR&quot;/&gt;
    &lt;warning group=&quot;VISIBILITY&quot; level=&quot;ERROR&quot;/&gt;
    &lt;warning group=&quot;CONSTANT_PROPERTY&quot; level=&quot;ERROR&quot;/&gt;
    ...
